content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were hosting an event at our home and just said goodnight to the last guest, my brother. a moment later, we heard knocking at the door. i knew it was my brother and assumed he forgot his phone or wallet and needed to get it before leaving. when i opened the door, my brother asked me to come out and see something strange. when i walked outside he pointed to two orange lights just above the tree line towards the northeast. i immediately dismissed the lights as aircraft. he corrected me and said they were moving unlike normal aircraft. he described the objects having moved parallel to each other before rotating and changing direction. again, i dismissed him as i only saw two orange lights. one was stationary and the other was moving similarly to an airplane. he asked me to note the orange nature of the objects and compare them to the light blue stars and the light blue lights of another obvious aircraft behind us. after the comparison, i did admit to the variation in light but simply dismissed the one moving object as an airplane. the other object i assumed was a planet due to its stationary position and orange glow. by this time, the moving object had disappeared behind the tree line while the stationary object remained in view. my brother attempted to explain the strange nature of the object's movements when, suddenly, the stationary orange dot began to move. this startled me. i watched with astonishment as the object moved along the sky and was temporarily obscured by the tree line before coming back into view. a moment later, the object faded away like an ember flickering and going out. i was honestly shocked and embarrassed by what i saw. i am not the type of person who likes attention or believes in intelligent extraterrestrial visitors. but i do believe in ufos... in the purely defined way of something being unidentified. and what i saw could not be identified. these dots of light were orange, looked like bright stars and appeared to be distant. my brother and i discussed the possibility of drones but these objects appeared to be quite high. i don't know much about drones, but i don't think they go that high and i don't think they have orange lights that flicker off. it was strange.
content.summary: Two orange objects moving unlike a plane

content.detailedDescription: Driveway. 0310 hrs. facing south. smoking cigarette. i see a bright object (not flashing) appearing in brightness as bright if not more than jupiter as bright as venus (our brightess celestial object.) travels briskly through the trees from the south-west and as it breaks through the trees facing south it appears to slow down as it sees me. it's flying as low if not lower than the aircraft flight paths that fly north and south of here and is unusual as it is flying between normal flight paths. it appears to slow down around south observation, bank and turn (still slowly) towards the east and continues slowly in the almost eastern direction. while i observed this change of direction observing towards the south i did see two other faint objects make a cross pattern behind the bright object: one to the right (w) and the other up (n?) after they passed and i could no longer see the first and initial brightest ufo fade east i seen the forth object come from north-e travelling south west. these can't be our satellites...Most of our newer ones are geo synchronous so they orbit the sun with the earth and do not move in the sky. older sats orbit the earth equatorially so the appear to cross the southern sky west to east (low earth orbit) in a rather slow appearance of time (or travel across the horizon north from the southern hemisphere) within a low degree should be less than 20 degrees. we do however have polar obit satellites but are rarely used to observe the earth and they travel north-south. they should not change direction as they have and will appear almost 90 degrees above if they do. i am an amateur astronomer and by the way, i have seen these occurances many times. i have witnessed more than 50 of the strange ufo occurances. this one topped the sightings since last summer and i felt estranged to report it. i have documented many of them but sometimes i have seen a few flying and hovering over my work at night (while on break 2230 hrs.) sometimes i've seen them flash brightly fade, then flash brightly and do this for less than 10 seconds and see them re-appear in another part of the sky and do this for less than 5-10 seconds. somehow they have ultralight craft...They skip off the upper atmopshere. they're not e.T. they're from our planet, some kind of advanced insect-or dolphin fish race

content.detailedDescription: I had just gone into my rear yard to put an empty bottle into the bin. as i lifted the lid i saw flashing lights in the sky. 4 red lights flashed brightly and when then faded there was a constant green band of light across the middle,seperating the top half from the bottom. at first i thought the police helicopter was out again, but as i watched i realised there was no noise. no noise at all. there were planes flying over as i live about 12 miles from manchester airport and i could hear those. it didnt seem to be moving at all. just flashing. i ran into the house and woke my partner up. i was excited. when you have cancelled everything else out, it could only be one thing. a ufo. i grabbed my phone and went back outside. my partner joined me and we both tried to work out just what it was. we both watched and agreed we had never seen anything like it before. after about 15 mins my partner went back in and left me to it. it seemed to be moving extremely slowly. in the 50 minutes i was watching i would say it had travelled approimately 10 miles. it seemed to be stopping at points. the lights looked to be brighter then but that might have been my eyes because it was dark. i watched planes of all altitudes travel across the sky and all were gone in less than five minutes. eventually it vanished behind the roof of the house behind ours. i tried to video it but my phone would zoom in far enough and being dark you couldnt see any thing but a small light. the video is jumpy because im at full zoom, so it is the phone not the object moving. you can see it flahing though.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription: Upon taking our puppy outside to go to the bathroom at approximately 9:41pm on sunday may 29th, 2016 my fiance and i observed a bright white light with (what looked to be) an orange colored ring or aura around it in the sky from our backyard. the direction in which the light was observed was nw from our home and very quickly disappeared there after. we decided to sit an watch for a while to see if it came back... it did at approximately 9:52pm. the light first appeared bright white, but when it dimmed, had an orange glow, flickered, pulsated-like, then dove down quickly at an angle out of view from our horizon focal point. over the course of about 3 hours, the light came and went but did not stay in view for very long. the light seemed to dim too much for video. however, i was able to take a few pictures in between observations (at full zoom on my iphone 6s plus). during that time, we witnessed the light change direction (from north to south and west to east), descend and ascend (from beyond the horizon out of view to above the horizon at about 10 degrees), emit orbs of light, disappear and re-appear, hover and sometimes follow a path or fly together with the orbs of light it had emitted.

content.detailedDescription: My son's and i were observing a rare display of thunder and lightning here in anchorage, and i was taking some video hoping to catch a cool streak of lighting and some thunder crashing and the like as we don't often get that sort of weather behavior in our part of alaska.  i noticed something out of my peripheral vision that seemed to climb rather quickly and seemingly close by.  the shape was peculiar, and i would describe as oblong, perhaps rectangular and the color was dark/black.  it ascended in a seemingly controlled manner, perhaps it was taking off, i'm not sure.  i called my children's attention to it and after ducking under a short overhang on our building and using the corner of the building to steady my arms as i tried to get the object into frame.  i noticed as it proceeded on its path across the city heading west from n/ne .  it was in the general vicinity of both merrill field, a small light aircraft  airport and jber (joint base elmendorf richardson) formerly elmendorf afb.  perhaps jber or merrill field has witness or radar confirmation as well.  the object seemed to turn and tumble in a very peculiar fashion.  it was quite larger than any balloon i've ever seen let loose and the way it moved and only ascended to a certain height seemed quite un-balloon like.   i was able to follow it for about 3 minutes or so until it was blocked out by buildings and a tree in the distance.  i have a cell phone video of the entire sighting, minus perhaps the first ascent.
content.summary: Saw black oblong/rectangular object ascend slightly, and continue on straight heading, tumbling and turning in an odd fashion

content.detailedDescription:
First of all, i want to express gratitude to this forum for allowing me to share my husband and i experience with a ufo. i recently found out about mufon and just have to report what happened to us a few years ago.

in april of 2012, my husband and i were walking to the market, which was directly across the street from us, when we observed an odd light directly above the apartments next to us. at first, we thought it may have been a reflection of the street lamp on something in the sky. as we continued walking, we kept looking at this light, which resembled a "tap light". the other odd thing was that neither of us spoke until my husband asked me if i was seeing what he was seeing. when we both acknowledged this "tap light", we stopped walking and stood there observing this light for about 10 minutes. we even looked around to see if anyone was seeing this "little moon" in the sky. the sky was dark but where this light was, it was even darker and when we continued to look at it, we noticed that behind the light was something that i still can't find the words to describe, so please bear with me.

the object behind the light didn't have a discernable shape. i couldn't see the object at first but i could see that this "tap light" was inset on the surface of something. the surface of the object was like the scrolling numbers on the movie "the matrix", that cut at angles to show that it had a shape but nothing i can definitively describe. it was as if a projector was shining on a plane surface rather than a white screen. also, the sky around this light was extremely dark. darker than the surrounding night sky. we stood there in disbelief because it was a friday night, and lots of people outside, yet no one but us was reacting to this thing in the sky. if my husband wasn't there with me, i may have thought i'd become insane. he confirmed what i was seeing with my own eyes and haven't told to anyone since then.

finally, after standing in the parking lot for what felt like a long time, we just walked away and went to the market. the object and its "tap light" was still there but wasn't there when we returned home. to me, i felt that this strange object was making itself invisible to everyone but because we first observed it from it's side, we were able to see it. 

though this in itself was a strange occurrence for both my husband and i, what happened the next few days after this event was even more strange. we started to notice our sleeping patterns were off and we both experienced a high sexual energy between us that felt very wrong to us, yet we had no control of.  it was like we couldn't keep our hands off each other and we couldn't be sated. also, my husband had a small puncture on his chest, like from a hypodermic needle. 

we don't have any pictures or video of this event because it was such a normal day, nothing warranted us to have our phones on us to take any. i wish we did because it was a truly amazing experience and has opened my eyes to things outside of the norm.
content.summary: Strange light with an odd object behind it that had a matrix-like surface

content.detailedDescription: Just before twilight on a overcast evening, my wife and i had just finished walking our dog and my wife sat down on a chair on the deck. i was standing across from her and looking across the road when i saw two strange large red orange lights rise from behind the white pine trees in the southern part of the sky heading in a south west - westerly direction. these orbs moved in a floaty but controlled way, but unlike any aircraft i know. as they traveled, they seemed to have subtly moved around as they headed on their trajectory. these two orbs were followed by four more in an identical way. my wife and i were completely amazed. i captured this event on my iphone. my wife told me that she saw two of them move together then apart as they were departing. it was difficult to believe what we were seeing. to our surprise, 10 minutes after the fist sighting, we saw two more of these same orbs acting in a similar manner to the first sighting and traveling in the same direction. these orbs were below cloud level and disappeared by fading into a small dot into the cloud covered sky.

content.detailedDescription:
I had just taken a shower and was walking to my bedroom when i noticed something out of my western facing windows.  i live on the top (6th) floor of a building in downtown cincinnati which has a commanding view of the western part of the city including union terminal.

it appeared to be spherical / oval in shape and intermittently flashed bright red light and silvery white lights on it's surface.  it's speed and altitude was fairly constant and not overly fast as it flew due north over the western part of the city at ~300 ft, then it climbed to ~1,000 ft and turned nne -- finally appearing to climb straight up into the clouds.

at first i thought it might be a helicopter (bell type) due to it's spherical shape but observed no tail or rotors.  the lights were strange because they almost looked like sunlight glinting off of the object or through it but the sun was almost directly above and behind cloud cover.
color of light was red particularly when the object was close, then almost bluish white when it was higher and farther away.  no noise.

i finally realized i had a camera nearby but it was pretty far away at that point and i didn't check the camera settings and unfortunately overexposed the picture.
content.summary: Observed sphere/oval object traveling n at low altitude, then and turning nne and climbing straight into clouds. craft emitted bright red and white light almost like reflections but brighter.

content.detailedDescription:
A friend and i were camping along the russian river in california, not far from novato, ca, on the pacific coast on a clear night, in 1971, probably during the late summer or early fall. 
     we were neither drinking nor under the influence of any drug. we were simply lying back, talking and looking at the starry sky.
     i noticed a fast-moving point of light from the northeast sweep into view, almost directly overhead. it was whitish with a faintly greenish cast to it, slightly larger and brighter than any of the stars in the background. against the backdrop of the starry sky, this light certainly appeared to be in motion close to earth, well within a distance measured in 100s to a few 1000s of feet. it was not a helicopter nor an airplane. 
     it also was not a "celestial" object such as a star or planet. it was not a firefly. it was not a campfire spark; we had no fire going. this silent point of light behaved with intention and swift precision within the atmosphere.
     both of us saw this light and watched it perform a short series of maneuvers: the point of light would swiftly and silently move to a new spot in the atmosphere (taking approx. 1 second) and then "stop on a dime". it would then remain stationary for several seconds, approx. 5 to 10 seconds at most. then, at an oblique angle, it would swiftly move to another position where it would again sit or hover silently.
     with our depth perception and an approximate sense of this moving light's distance away/above us, an estimate of 1000 feet would be the distance it traveled in approx. 1 second between the "pause points".
     this pattern -- a swift straight line movement to a single stopping point; remaining still for several seconds, then moving to another point -- repeatedly continued for about 5 to 7 minutes. finally, it shot out of sight in a straight line into a northerly direction, slightly to the west.
     we did not know then, nor know now, of any aircraft or aerial phenomenon that could account for such activities, especially when no sound was associated with the movement. we noted that the hamilton air force base was somewhat nearby, yet the aerial movement of this light-object was unlike any aircraft technology known to us.
     so, indeed, we were experiencing an unidentified flying object.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering
content.summary: Silent lighted small form swept fast into view, hovered perfectly still, then bee-lined fast to hover at another position. this activity continued for 5-7 minutes.

content.detailedDescription:
It was a darker cloudy sky that night, just before sunset, many darker grey clouds in the sky.

there were really two phenomenons in this one sighting, one that i have seen before in a sky similar to the one that night, darker clouds.  here and there at sunset in this kind of sky i became aware of what looked like headlights in the dark clouds as if something was looking through high beams to see through the dark clouds.  i know this to be a strange phenomenon because the distance between the 'headlights' seemed the same in the pairs of 'headlights' i saw that night and on other occassions in a similar sky as i have said.  if the two 'headlights' were different in spaces between them i probably wouldn't have noticed.

also i noticed that here and there in that sky there were also groups of 3 white bright lights like the 'headlights' but they seemed to form a solid object, triangle.  i saw maybe a dozen or more sets of 'headlights' and maybe 3 or 4 triangles.

both the triangle lights and 'headlight' lights were bright white as headlights would be on earth and white.  they didn't move but started to dim here and there and then poof they were gone.  others would appear then dim and out like the others.

for some reason i found myself looking at one point between two very dark clouds that had a lighter grey area inbetween them and all of a sudden i witnessed a white fuzzy edged solid looking disc moving from the dark cloud to the right across the lighter grey area to the dark cloud to the left - a trip that lasted about 5 seconds max.  startled me.  it was moving to hide behind a second cloud is what it looked like.  it didn't move too quickly, just changing location.  it moved on a bit of an angle up, like just under say 45 degrees.  i didn't see that disc again that night.

as i said before i have seen these 'headlights' often in this type of sky.
content.summary: In dark clouded sky at sunset 'headlights' of something in sky, approx 10 or so at a time plus disc shaped object going from one cloud to another

content.detailedDescription: I was in my backyard smoking a cigarette and noticed 5 lights above my head that looked like stars flying in a v formation from west to east/south east at about the one o'clock position i could see a dull grey outline around each object as if reflecting light from ground below at about the 2 o'clock position the objects looked like lights again then they changed from in a v formation and lined up in a straight line from 2'oclock position to 3'oclock position then back to v formation at about the 4'oclock position and traveled across the sky all the way until they couldn't be seen anymore still traveling east/southeast
content.summary: 5 boomerang objects in v formation then to a straight line then back to v formation

content.detailedDescription: My neighbor and i were outside at night and we witnessed something that was definitely not a plane.  we noticed it was flying over really slow like it was scanning or looking for something.  it changed speeds going slower and made absolutely no noise and it was as low like a plane getting ready to land.  we had watched it come from nowhere then after almost 10 minutes it just was gone.  we were both amazed and did not leave us feeling scared like the other ones.
content.summary: It came out of no where and we waited to hear noise but it was no plane and it flew to slow to be a plane. it was a amazing sight

content.detailedDescription: Taos,believed these objects flew out from the rio grande gorge,i first spotted the objects when i turned on road 110,they looked to be  fly over my neighborhood,dancing and circling,then merged as one. i called my brother at approximately at 9:32pm to tell him to look outside,he didn't answer so i rushed thru the neighborhood home and got him to come outside.We watched for about 5 minutes trying to get cameras etc then the object flew west very fast,unable to get film or video,damit!
content.summary: 2 glowing fireball dancing in the sky that merged into one then flew quick west at phenomenal rate of speed

content.detailedDescription: I was on my back patio having coffee and i saw a white oval object in slow motion moving across the sky in a straight line and there was another one 15 minutes later doing the same thing and then they just blended with the sky.It was partially cloudy.There were no planes in sight or heard.What is going on in jupiter's skies ?
content.summary: I saw 2 of these objects within 15 minutes of each other.
